{"aar_log_filter":{"content_index":0,"dropped_prefix_bytes":1786,"field":"text","message":"earlier repeated message_update events dropped","replaced_fields":2,"response_id":"gen-1782786426-Ba7awF7fkyZaTYdEbvdF","tail_bytes":3},"assistantMessageEvent":{"contentIndex":0,"delta":"**.","partial":{"api":"openai-completions","content":[{"text":"**.","type":"text"}],"model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1782786426-Ba7awF7fkyZaTYdEbvdF","role":"assistant","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782786426094,"usage":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"input":0,"output":0,"total":0},"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0}},"type":"text_delta"},"message":{"api":"openai-completions","content":[{"text":"**.","type":"text"}],"model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1782786426-Ba7awF7fkyZaTYdEbvdF","role":"assistant","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782786426094,"usage":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"input":0,"output":0,"total":0},"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0}},"type":"message_update"}
{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_start","contentIndex":1,"partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my careful review of the record, the key issue is whether the admitted evidence demonstrates by a preponderance that this operation had the objective of \"removing the sitting government\" as defined in the proposition, rather than merely being a capture operation that falls under the \"capture of a head of state without territorial occupation\" carve-out.\n\nThe evidence clearly shows:\n- U.S. ground forces entered Caracas, Venezuela in January 2026 in a military operation\n- The operation was combat-capable and involved special operations forces\n- Maduro was captured and removed from Venezuela\n\nHowever, the crucial question is the objective. The proposition specifically distinguishes between:\n1. \"removing the sitting government\" (would resolve YES)\n2. \"capture of a head of state without territorial occupation\" (explicitly resolves NO based on the edge case)\n\nThe admitted evidence, particularly from PX-1 (Defense Department source), shows that the stated objective was \"to bring outlaw dictator Nicolas Maduro to justice\" and the operation is described as a \"capture\" and \"extraction.\" While there is language about Maduro being \"out of power\" and the U.S. overseeing a transition, this appears to be describing the political aftermath rather than the stated military objective.\n\nThe preponderance standard requires me to find that the evidence makes it more likely than not that the objective was governmental removal rather than the capture operation that the proposition explicitly excludes. Given the specificity of the edge case language and the consistent characterization of this as a capture/extraction operation throughout the official sources, I cannot find that the plaintiff has met their burden.\n\nI will vote that the proposition has **not been demonstrated**."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019f165a539c0a8383aa27cc314cbc6d","name":"mcp","arguments":{},"partialArgs":"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782786426094,"responseId":"gen-1782786426-Ba7awF7fkyZaTYdEbvdF"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my careful review of the record, the key issue is whether the admitted evidence demonstrates by a preponderance that this operation had the objective of \"removing the sitting government\" as defined in the proposition, rather than merely being a capture operation that falls under the \"capture of a head of state without territorial occupation\" carve-out.\n\nThe evidence clearly shows:\n- U.S. ground forces entered Caracas, Venezuela in January 2026 in a military operation\n- The operation was combat-capable and involved special operations forces\n- Maduro was captured and removed from Venezuela\n\nHowever, the crucial question is the objective. The proposition specifically distinguishes between:\n1. \"removing the sitting government\" (would resolve YES)\n2. \"capture of a head of state without territorial occupation\" (explicitly resolves NO based on the edge case)\n\nThe admitted evidence, particularly from PX-1 (Defense Department source), shows that the stated objective was \"to bring outlaw dictator Nicolas Maduro to justice\" and the operation is described as a \"capture\" and \"extraction.\" While there is language about Maduro being \"out of power\" and the U.S. overseeing a transition, this appears to be describing the political aftermath rather than the stated military objective.\n\nThe preponderance standard requires me to find that the evidence makes it more likely than not that the objective was governmental removal rather than the capture operation that the proposition explicitly excludes. Given the specificity of the edge case language and the consistent characterization of this as a capture/extraction operation throughout the official sources, I cannot find that the plaintiff has met their burden.\n\nI will vote that the proposition has **not been demonstrated**."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019f165a539c0a8383aa27cc314cbc6d","name":"mcp","arguments":{},"partialArgs":"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782786426094,"responseId":"gen-1782786426-Ba7awF7fkyZaTYdEbvdF"}}
