"capture of a head of state without territorial occupation\" (explicitly resolves NO based on the edge case)\n\nThe admitted evidence, particularly from PX-1 (Defense Department source), shows that the stated objective was \"to bring outlaw dictator Nicolas Maduro to justice\" and the operation is described as a \"capture\" and \"extraction.\" While there is language about Maduro being \"out of power\" and the U.S. overseeing a transition, this appears to be describing the political aftermath rather than the stated military objective.\n\nThe preponderance standard requires me to find that the evidence makes it more likely than not that the objective was governmental removal rather than the capture operation that the proposition explicitly excludes. Given the specificity of the edge case language and the consistent characterization of this as a capture/extraction operation throughout the official sources, I cannot find that the plaintiff has met their burden.\n\nI will vote that the proposition has **not been demonstrated**."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019f165a539c0a8383aa27cc314cbc6d","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\": \"not_demonstrated\", \"rationale\": \"While the record clearly shows U.S. ground forces entered Caracas in a combat operation that captured Maduro, the proposition's explicit edge case for 'capture of a head of state without territorial occupation' applies here. The official sources"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\": \\\"not_demonstrated\\\", \\\"rationale\\\": \\\"While the record clearly shows U.S. ground forces entered Caracas in a combat operation that captured Maduro, the proposition's explicit edge case for 'capture of a head of state without territorial occupation' applies here. The official sources","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"