 territorial occupation required to escape the carve-out.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\": \\\"not_demonstrated\\\", \\\"rationale\\\": \\\"While the record clearly shows U.S. ground forces entered Caracas in a combat operation that captured Maduro, the proposition's explicit edge case for 'capture of a head of state without territorial occupation' applies here. The official sources consistently characterize this as a capture/extraction/justice operation rather than demonstrating the objective of governmental removal or territorial occupation required to escape the carve-out.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782786426094,"responseId":"gen-1782786426-Ba7awF7fkyZaTYdEbvdF"}}
